Important:
The tool cannot know whether SQL truly runs unless we execute it against the database.
So do not claim "runnable".
Instead:
- perform static checks only
- classify as "assumed_runnable" if SQL exists and has SELECT/FROM
- classify as "failed_static_check" if SQL is missing or structurally incomplete
- otherwise use "unknown"

